videoSnippet.title: Best Part of a Chess Game Often Goes Unseen
videoSnippet.description:

Ian Nepomniachtchi vs Mikhail Antipov
Russian Championship Superfinal, ROUND 4
Sicilian, Najdorf (B90)

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. a3 e5 7. Nf3 h6 8. Bc4 Be6 9. Bb3 Nc6 10. O-O Rc8 11. h3 Be7 12. Nh2 O-O 13. Ng4 Nxg4 14. hxg4 Bg5 15. Nd5 Nd4 16. c3 Bxc1 17. Rxc1 Nxb3 18. Qxb3 Bxg4 19. Qxb7 Rb8 20. Qxa6 Rxb2 21. Rb1 Be2 22. Qc6 Rd2 23. Rfe1 Qg5 24. Rxe2 Rxe2 25. Qxd6 Re8 26. Qd7 Re6 27. g3 Qh5 28. Kg2 Kh7 29. Qd8 Qg4 30. Rb4 Rg6

The 73rd Russian Championship is a 12-player round-robin tournament taking place from 5-16 December 2020 in the Central Chess Club in Moscow, Russia.

Players receive 90 minutes for 40 moves, followed by 30 minutes to the end of the game, plus a 30-second increment starting from move one. Official website: ruchess.ru
